{"id": "1406357210908459100", "channel_id": "1406357210908459100", "type": 0, "author_id": "356954731681284107", "author_name": "statjunkie", "author_bot": false, "content": "Hi! Been playing for 6 days.\nThe 3 images are: my current lineup, and then my full unit roster. My sense is that Faint is a “lose less” character, and I would rather play a “win more” character that supports my active strategy. But the other three units feel quite strong, and have a medium-good amount of synergy (Jenkin, Thais, Salvador). I generally use Thais for extra copies of Jenkin’s 1-cost to continue amping damage. I’m mostly curb-stomping the content through Normal Chapter 3, but I don’t want to continue investing if I’ll regret it later.\n\nSo, should I:\n- Dump Jenkin & Faint, and replace them with Caechs & Goliath?\n- Dump Faint for Winkle (I dropped Winkle before because she felt off.)\n- Uvhash or something for full Caro?\n- Other?\n\nI mostly want to future-proof my investment for future content. (Currently planning to use my store dupe for Thais E1 and continue pulling for her E2.) I really like Caro’s mechanics. I feel okay about Ultra’s mechanics. Never even tried tentacles for a single fight yet.", "timestamp": "2025-08-16T19:21:27.934000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1406357211835273307", "filename": "IMG_9394.png", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 1556308, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1406357210908459100/1406357211835273307/IMG_9394.png?ex=69ccc778&is=69cb75f8&hm=f4312365c5c0f37637f744e2f4a2aa5d00aee8b290bf5ac6d675d9e4e02e2623&"}, {"id": "1406357212598767646", "filename": "IMG_9395.png", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 915794, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1406357210908459100/1406357212598767646/IMG_9395.png?ex=69ccc778&is=69cb75f8&hm=a4026baa36d3b71facefe9d9a96bd09ed8168dc3a1613c29973afb0dbcd7509c&"}, {"id": "1406357213026451609", "filename": "IMG_939