{"id": "1406212043845144606", "channel_id": "1404957539992338442", "type": 0, "author_id": "272394963642220545", "author_name": "__goz__", "author_bot": false, "content": "Packing your ultra space full of 1-costs is only really good if you have some strength, since you get to proc the double strength scaling (on **Leap**) for all of them.\nOtherwise the multihit is really good, and you should be trying to send it for some good damage.\n\nDepending on your comp you can absolutely yield the [*first card played in turn*] priority, especially to units with **Quasar** such as Clem or Castor. Unless it's a swarm of rats, you take their effects any day of the week.\n\nFor the Ultra turn vs Annihilation (=*destroy 1 card for Insight*) choice :\n- I like Ultra turn, it really makes use of Jenkins' double scaling when you exalt during ultra turn, and having stored mice swarms mean insane damage, you can just come into a bossfight with an big ultra turn prepared and wipe it turn 1;\n- Annihilation as said above will allow you to play the swarm same turn as cast, and for me that's about it : you get to grab a little more damage, but overall you don't play into your biggest strength.\n\nNote that for anything other than 100% Ultra or Ultra + Chaos mix, you get reduced damage during the ultra turn, so it's not really something you'd want for Jenkins, and if you plan on playing such comps, you should get familiar with annihilation, as you will most likely get more value from it.", "timestamp": "2025-08-16T09:44:37.409000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1404957539992338442", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Needing help on building Jenkin", "forum_channel_id": "1356200968311803956", "thread_tags": ["1400747088995811358"]}
